A [[mining pool|Pooled_mining]] originally created for the [Ars Technica](http://arstechnica.com) community.  The pool is open to the public.

This pool pays out using a proportional share reward system (your shares / total shares for the round) = % share of the rewards.

The service was first available on June 15, 2011.
It was announced on the Bitcoin forums on June 17th, 2011.

##Reward distribution

* Proportional: 0% fee.

